column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Calm- dark- cloudy- have had 5 days of rain.
Water slightly brown- 2 baby loons- family of fishers north of lake.
Cabbage plants never reached the surface.
The cabbage weeds are tall this year.  Two baby loons.
The sun looks orange because of the forest fires.
The lake level only goes up an inch or so because the lake flows into White Birch- Bob's Lake and on.  Last reading.
Sunny + calm.  No blue herons this year.
We had a fish kill. I have only seen dead fish.  We had brown water when the ice went out.
Very quiet!  No boats- fish- or birds.
Few boats because of fish kill 2 years ago.
Many eagles- loons- blue herons- etc.
Lake choppy.  Readings taken the day after very strong winds.
Very windy- 15-21 mph gusts.  Water near whitecaps and stirred up.
The temperature and dissolved oxygen are from 6/9/99.
(NO DATA SHEET REC`D FOR BOTTOM- SHEET CREATED + DATE-STAMPED 10/25)
